{"ts": "2026-06-07T21:21:16.046838+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "## Answer\n\n### Installed command-line tool: **`gwc`** (Git Workflow Companion)\n\nThe package name is `gwc` (version 0.1.0). When you run `pip install -e .` in the repository root, it registers a `gwc` entry point at `gwc.cli:main` (as defined in `pyproject.toml`).\n\n### What `gwc` currently does\n\nRunning `gwc` requires a subcommand. The implemented subcommands are:\n\n| Subcommand | What it does |\n|---|---|\n| **`gwc status-summary`** | Prints a single-line summary of the current branch:<br>• branch name<br>• ahead/behind counts vs. its tracked upstream (or `(no upstream)` if none)<br>• counts of staged, unstaged, and untracked files<br><br>Example output:<br>`feature/login  (ahead 2, behind 0)  staged=1 unstaged=3 untracked=0` |\n| **`gwc branch-name <issue> <slug>`** | Generates a conventional branch name like `issue-42-add-login` (prefix configurable via `.gwcrc`). Does **not** create the branch — only prints the name. |\n| **`gwc clean-merged`** | Lists local branches that are fully merged into `main`. By default runs in **dry-run** mode (just prints what *would* be deleted). Pass `--apply` to actually delete them. |\n\nThere is also a `--version` flag (`gwc --version`) that prints `gwc 0.1.0`.\n\n*Note:* The source docstring mentions a `sync` subcommand as a legacy alias, but it is **not** wired into the argument parser and is not currently available.\n\nAll the heavy lifting is done via thin wrappers around `git` subprocess calls in `src/gwc/git_ops.py`, with optional settings read from `./.gwcrc` (TOML) in the repository root.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 739, "prompt_tokens": 5699, "total_tokens": 6438, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 299, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 5504}, "prompt_cache_hit_tokens": 5504, "prompt_cache_miss_tokens": 195}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "deepseek-v4-flash", "system_fingerprint": "fp_8b330d02d0_prod0820_fp8_kvcache_20260402", "id": "72edb391-4043-49e6-bca6-3c8877b68441", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea3f6-00b8-7c82-8c0f-afce4f7b51e7-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 5699, "output_tokens": 739, "total_tokens": 6438, "input_token_details": {"cache_read": 5504}, "output_token_details": {"reasoning": 299}}}}]}}}
